  "texts": [
    "In daily life, hypotheses are used constantly, and mostly unconsciously.",
    "For example, while driving on a busy highway, the decision to change lanes is based on hypotheses related to prior experiences, the surrounding vehicles' behavior, and relative speeds and distances among all these vehicles.",
    "Most drivers can maneuver successfully without explicitly articulating which step is hypothesis generation and which is hypothesis testing.",
    "This process occurs very rapidly and is usually not accomplished consciously.",
    "Many hypothesis generations refer to everyday hypotheses."
  ],
